-- China Academic Sees Second-Quarter Growth at 10.6%, Securities Times Says
-- Bloomberg News
-- 2010-07-04T23:37:28Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-04/china-academic-sees-second-quarter-growth-at-10-6-securities-times-says.html

          
          
             China’s second-quarter economic
growth may be 10.6 percent, the Securities Times reported,
citing Pei Changhong, director of the institute of finance and
trade economics at the China Academy of Social Sciences.  
 The nation’s economy may grow 10.1 percent in the third
quarter, 9.3 percent in the fourth quarter and 10.5 percent for
the full year, the Shenzhen-based newspaper reported, citing
Pei.  
 Second-quarter consumer prices may gain 3.04 percent, the
newspaper reported, citing Pei. Consumer prices may gain 3.3
percent in the third quarter and 2.2 percent in the fourth
quarter, the newspaper reported, citing Pei.  
